The paper uses satellite imagery and deep learning to predict infrastructure quality in Africa, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of spatial interpolation, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and spatial information (cs.SI).
